The way Iâ€™d approach the video would be to do what I call â€œafter the factâ€ Sketchnoting. Have your audience take â€œregularâ€ handwritten notes while they watch the video. Then, have them review the notes and then create their Sketchnote. This does two things.

It does 2 things. 1) takes the pressure off of creating the sketchnote while watching the video. 2) has them review the information they already captured in their notes and filter it for importance when deciding what to include in the Sketchnote.

After the fact Sketchnoting gives so many more interactions with the information. 1) taking traditional notes 2) reviewing notes to decide what to use in SN 3) the act of creating the Sketchnote itself. Thatâ€™s 3 different interactions with info.
Usually we take notes and put them away never to look at them again. With after the fact they see the info and process it 3 times.

After a couple of days of playing through Smash post Joker DLC, I think I've concluded that Challenger Pack 1 with Joker, Mementos and songs from P3-5 is the best DLC content we've received for any Smash game.

First of all Joker plays beautifully (new main watch out). But the references and love Sakurai has given the Persona franchise is great. Atlus has reciprocated the love by putting music from not only P5 but 3 and 4 too. Wow, thank you.

I state that specifically because the next best character inclusion was Cloud in Smash 4. But it was kinda sketchy. Square Enix only gave us two songs for the entire FF franchise... It's great to see Atlus giving love to Smash as a third party.

Other than that, everything about pack 1 is fantastic. I can't wait to see who they pick next. My guess is Erdrick, Sora (if he's not next it's never happening ever), or Banjo. Please be Banjo I'll actually cry.
